<TITLE> Man arrested as a militant suspect </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com)  Police Friday detained a suspected militant from Baitul Mokarram national mosque before Juma prayers. They are questioning Rokon Uddin Mahmud. Duty officer of Paltan Police Station sub-inspector Monir Hossain said Mahmud stood up before the khutba in the mosque and tried to say something. Later the devotees turned him in to police. A copy of the Quran, some Arabic papers and leaflets were seized from him. Mahmud said his home was in Jhenaigati in Sherpur. He came here to visit his brother. The police officer said the man was apparently suffering from mental disorders and was speaking incoherently. He also said he was a student. bdnews
